com.navis.framework.persistence.util

Enum DatabaseDataType

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<DatabaseDataType>
      • com.navis.framework.persistence.util.DatabaseDataType
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<DatabaseDataType>

    public enum DatabaseDataType
extends java.lang.Enum<DatabaseDataType>
    This class enumerates all database type which N4 applications could have. Some of them are quite rare and undesirable, some could be easily substituted. For postgres we use aliases. This enum includes types for following databses: Oracle, Sqlserver, Postgres and MySql. Some types are common for a few databases.

    * @author Andrey Ignatenko, 6/8/2015
